Full job description

Function/Duties of Position:
This position is for a research data analyst 1 in the Oregon Center for Aging & Technology (ORCATECH) at OHSU as part of a team of researchers and technical staff who work together to create tools and systems for assessing changes in memory and motor function in the elderly, using unobtrusive in-home sensor systems. This person will work with ORCATECH faculty on the curation of digital biomarker data to create data sets for both internal and external analysis, manage and create ORCATECH Qualtrics surveys and data, and assist with limited data analysis and data visualizations.
Required Qualifications:
  • Masters' degree in relevant field OR
  • Bachelors in relevant field AND 2 years of relevant experience
  • Experience with Qualtrics or other electronic survey
  • Experience with digital biomarker data such as output from wearables devices, digital scales, etc.
  • Experience with python, R or other programming language used for data manipulation and analysis
  • Strong computer skills (including Microsoft OS and productivity software)
  • Critical thinking skills and the ability to learn and integrate new information quickly
  • Ability to speak and communicate clearly
  • Demonstrate a high level of professionalism
  • High level of responsibility and ability to work independently
  • Ability to prioritize work demands and manage time appropriately
  • Organizational skills and ability to multitask
Preferred Qualifications:
  • Research experience; familiarity with research methods
Why apply to OHSU?: Oregon Health & Science University values a diverse and culturally competent workforce. We are proud of our commitment to being an equal opportunity, affirmative action organization that does not discriminate against applicants on the basis of any protected class status, including disability status and protected veteran status. Individuals with diverse backgrounds and those who promote diversity and a culture of inclusion are encouraged to apply. To request reasonable accommodation contact the Affirmative Action and Equal Opportunity Department at 503-494-5148 or aaeo@ohsu.edu.
